editorialSummary.text: Drugstore chain with health & beauty aids, prescriptions & photo services, plus mini-mart basics.

originalText.text: If I could give zero stars I would. I have been disconnected by the pharmacy at least 6 times and can’t reach anyone on the phone. This is a joke of customer service.

originalText.text: Went here to pick up a package, but needed some items so I went to the deodorant isle. An old, black bald man was stocking products, and as to not interrupt him, i pressed the customer service button for assistance. He looked and asked “was that you?” (Who pressed the button), I responded “I needed…” and before I could finish my sentence he rudely said “IM RIGHT HERE…YOU ONLY PRESS THE BUTTON IF THERES NO ONE HERE…” I responded;  “sorry, I thought you were busy and didn’t want to interrupt you….I needed two items; a razor and deodorant.”  He unlocked the razor area and I grabbed my item, then headed to the deodorant area. I look up and he was gone…just walked away saying something either to someone or under his breath. Please know I only come here for a convenience, not for the customer service. The young lady that helped me retrieve my package at the register was cool, but homeboy and the deodorant and razor aisle needs a chill pill,  and maybe be a pay raise. That might get rid of his grumpy demeanor.
